snippet.title: Vlogging in Paris with my Dad
snippet.description:
Wandering and vlogging through Paris with my dad and spending all of my words on him, few on the camera. I shot a lot of Paris footage and hardly any speaking - I barely realized that. Help me make better videos at http://patreon.com/jayswanson and then find me on the internet in all of the usual spots:
http://twitter.com/jayonaboat
http://instagram.com/jayswanson (me) http://instagram.com/mindofjayswanson (books)
http://facebook.com/jay.swanson.author

Music by: Joakim Karud

My name is Jay Swanson - I'm an American writer daily vlogging in Paris on an artist visa and hoping to make the city of light my home base - at least for the foreseeable future. I write science-fiction and fantasy, vlog daily, and love pizza a little too much.

FAQ:
How long have you lived in France? On and off for over two years.

What do you miss most about ho- NACHOS

You're always talking about living on some ship. WHAT SHIP? - I made a "Draw My Life" video that explains a lot here: https://youtu.be/-MrvL37jTKM

Where are you from originally? - Pullman, Washington - a small university/agricultural town near Idaho (and yes, the potatoes are amazing).

What do you film with? - I currently film almost exclusively with my Samsung Galaxy S8: http://amzn.to/2lPKSpZ

How do you get those shots where you're walking or running? - A Joby Gorillapod for smartphones, like this: http://amzn.to/2sXNIL3

You drop your phone a lot, how does it survive? - THIS CASE IS AMAZING: http://amzn.to/2hoxgTA (Galaxy S7) - http://amzn.to/2Dt08Bu (Galaxy S8) - http://amzn.to/2FxVliP (iPhone)

What do you edit with? - Adobe Premiere - it's pretty much all I've ever used since high school.

Aren't you ever freaked out by leaving your camera behind to film yourself? - Yep. But not too badly - I tend to be careful when I do.

Why are you living in #Paris? - Because I've always wanted to; I feel at home here: https://youtu.be/4Vivf6MqMxQ

But what are you doing there? - Living it up! https://youtu.be/ZW2RP--DO8Y

Do you speak French? Oui. https://youtu.be/va1QjaHgij8

You talk a lot about the books you're working on, what are they about? - They're sci-fi (and fantasy) and I've got a decent pitch for you here: https://youtu.be/W2bKt4_Tp4E

Do you make money off YouTube? - Ha, no. I wish. It took me over 500 videos to make my first $100 off adsense. I think it will slowly change, but VERY slowly.

I really enjoy your videos, how can I support you? - The easiest and best way to support me is through Patreon, where you can pitch in as little as $1/mo to help me make better videos: http://patreon.com/jayswanson

I don't trust this Patreon thing - what's your PayPal? - Here's a handy link! https://www.paypal.me/jayswanson

I like PayPal in pink! - Here's my ko-fi if that's your thing (and coffee is your game): https://ko-fi.com/jayswanson

But I want to send you something tangible! - I do have a wishlist on Amazon, though it's a bit complicated with the international shipping situation. This is the US one: http://amzn.to/2ykS9Ux

And here's the French one: http://bit.ly/JaysFrenchWishList

Can I come stay with you in Paris? - Have you seen my apartment? It's too small for me as it is! https://youtu.be/6t2qj3rdyX8

OK, but how do I use the Metro when I'm there? - I made a handy video for you: https://youtu.be/T0YS5si8bJs

comments.textDisplay: So enjoyed watching the wanderings of the Swanson men in Paris!!! Flowers looking lovely to liven things up at 2:28! So glad I'm not the only person who remembers the mantra of "when in Europe, always look UP" for all that meticulous ceiling beauty and craftsmanship like you did around 3:24 & 3:32. It always amazed me when traveling abroad how much detail went into all aspects of the creation of most every old monument, artifact, artifice and church/cathedral! I cannot wait to see more father son vlogs as you two roam the city, once again creating an awesome vicarious escape from reality for myself! Just make sure you guys BOTH make enough time to get some SLEEP (you know, that foreign concept you keep hearing about Jay😂😴) 😍💕✌!

comments.textDisplay: I don’t how how you fit in the editing time, but the jump cuts were as delightful as opening the fridge and realizing there is, indeed enough hummus left to feed a starving moment. I love sweet surprises! Some are already mentioned, but the father/son stair sequence at 1:14, the light catching windows in time with the keyboard descant at 2:12, and the flickering lights matching the 16th/32nd notes at 4:38 are just so sweet. Your love of music shines through those and other moments. Also; love seeing the legacy/hereditary aspect of your oft used ‘thumbs up’. 😊

comments.textDisplay:
I laughed at the vacation comment because when you are LIVING in a foreign country you are not on vacation. You have the same daily routine and daily living challenges of fitting everything into your day.....just as you would ANYWHERE you lived. So many people fall into the illusion that it's being on vacation 24/7/365. I think it's why there are so many unrealistic expectations about moving to a foreign country. If anything life is even more challenging because while they roll out the red carpet to VISITORS it is extremely difficult to earn the right to actually LIVE there. Unlike our country who opens the door wide and, in my opinion, makes it too easy to live here when you are not from the U.S.
You made a wonderful point Jay even though it wasn't directly stated! I used to get that all the time. .....or (huge lol) people think you are really rich and living on vacation! !
